headline: ENPH Q4 Deep Dive: Product Innovation and Channel Strategies Drive Optimism Amid Revenue Decline
summary: Home energy technology company Enphase (NASDAQ:ENPH) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales fell by 10.3% year on year to $343.3 million. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($285 million at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 8.3% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.71 per share was 21.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
